.TH "wayshot" "1" "2025-03-26" "github.com/waycrate/wayshot" "General Commands Manual"
.PP
.SH NAME
.PP
Wayshot - Screenshot tool for compositors implementing zwlr_screencopy_v1 such as sway and river
.PP
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\fBwayshot\fR [\fIoptions\fR] [\fIoutput\fR]
.PP
.SH ARGUMENTS
.PP
\fBoutput\fR,
.RS 4
Location to send captured screenshot to, it can be of the following types:
.RS 4
1.\& A directory, image outputs will be saved in the default format "wayshot-yyyy-mm-dd-hh-mm-ss.\&png"
.PP
2.\& A path (Encoding is automatically inferred from the extension).\&
.PP
3.\& '\&-'\& which sends the screenshot to stdout.\&
.PP
.RE
The \fB--clipboard\fR option can also be used simultaneously with any of the above to copy the image to the clipboard too.\& 
.PP
.RE
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
\fB-h\fR,
.RS 4
Print concise help messages and quit.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB--help\fR,
.RS 4
Print full help message and quit.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-V\fR, \fB--version\fR
.RS 4
Print version information.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB--log-level <LOG_LEVEL>\fR
.RS 4
Log level to be used for printing to stderr  
Possible values: trace, debug, info, warn, error
.PP
Default value: info
.PP
.RE
\fB-c\fR, \fB--cursor\fR
.RS 4
Enable cursor visibility in screenshots.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB--clipboard\fR
.RS 4
Copy image contents to clipboard also.\& 
Using this flag will cause the wayshot process to fork and persist in the background offering the image
on the wayland clipboard until some other program overwrites the clipboard.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-e\fR, \fB--extension\fR
.RS 4
Set the image encoder.\& Without this option, encoding is either inferred from the \fBoutput\fR filename or defaults to png.\&  
Valid arguments:
.RS 4
.PD 0
.IP \(bu 4
jpg
.IP \(bu 4
png (Default encoder)
.IP \(bu 4
ppm
.IP \(bu 4
qoi
.IP \(bu 4
webp
.IP \(bu 4
avif
.PD
.PP
.RE
.RE
\fB-l\fR, \fB--list-outputs\fR
.RS 4
List all valid output names.\& This flag is generally used in combination with \fB-o\fR flag.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB--choose-output\fR
.RS 4
Present a fuzzy selector for display (wl_output) selection.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-o\fR, \fB--output\fR
.RS 4
Choose a particular display (wl_output) to screenshot.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-s\fR, \fB--slurp\fR=<SLURP_ARGS>
.RS 4
If this option is passed, wayshot takes a screenshot first and then uses the \fBslurp\fR program to select a portion of that screenshot
https://github.\&com/emersion/slurp .\& SLURP_ARGS are any arguments that need to be passed to \fBslurp\fR, see \fBslurp(1)\fR for more information.\&
.PP
Example:
\fBwayshot -s="-b 11223377"\fR
.PD 0
.IP \(bu 4
This takes a screenshot then calls slurp with "-b 11223377" as an argument for cropping the screenshot.\&
.PD
.PP
.RE
\fB--file-name-format\fR
.RS 4
Output file name'\&s formatting.\& Refer to chrono formatting rules: https://docs.\&rs/chrono/latest/chrono/format/strftime/index.\&html.\&
.PP
Example: --file-name-format "%Y_%m_%d-%H_%M_%S"
.PP
Default: wayshot-%Y_%m_%d-%H_%M_%S
.PP
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.RS 4
.PD 0
.IP \(bu 4
wayshot(7)
.PD
.PP
.RE
